<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1491,2020]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,1491,1516]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Identification.</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity box="[530,673,1491,1515]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.15" metricValueMax="8.1" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="7.15" valueMax="8.1" valueMin="6.2">6.2–8.1 mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[687,949,1492,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Dyspyralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticosta">
<emphasis box="[687,949,1492,1516]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Dyspyralis puncticosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a dirty white forewing ground color. Forewing markings include an irregular shaped, black spot on costa that extends to M vein; antemedial line black, originating from a black spot on costa line angled toward wing base then angled toward outer margin, then angled back toward wing base to posterior margin; postmedial line black, originating from a black spot on costa, slightly sinuate, never a solid line but consisting of a series of irregular black scales; terminal area mostly brown; terminal line black, a series of spots between veins. 
<collectingCountry box="[643,699,1671,1695]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing is light brown with no discal spot. Anterior half of tegulae and mesothorax are black. Abdomen has a prominent, dorsal black scale tuft with white apices between the second and third segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1491,2020]" box="[197,589,1779,1804]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,360,1779,1804]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Flight period.</emphasis>
